C. B. BUCHANAN, A. Cellers, J. W. Bailey, and H. F. Reese, Petitioners, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Respondent. No. 6598. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 29, 1931.

Before WILBUR and SAWTELLE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for respondent, consented to by counsel for petitioners, ordered petition to review in above cause dismissed without prejudice to rights of any of the parties; mandate forthwith. •
